timelineItems.name: Michael Norton
timelineItems.text: Reds looking a little better, Gio and Jozy looking intimidating. But just not enough space for them to really do anything #NYCvTOR #TFCLive

timelineItems.name: Jeff Weisinger
timelineItems.text: Mullins with a low rocket to the right of Konopka, but the shot goes just wide of the net. Near quick goal for @NYCFC. #NYCvTOR, 0-0, 11'

timelineItems.name: Nick ChÃ¡vez
timelineItems.text: .@TaylorTwellman: "Kreis knew what he was getting into" with City Football Group. You would certainly think so and hope so. #NYCFC

timelineItems.name: Sixth Borough Blues
timelineItems.text: 13. Mullins with a brilliant work-rate. Constantly looking to make runs further up the field. #NYCFC #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Peter Nolan
timelineItems.text: Wingert shot turned away. Great Pirlo feed to Grabavoy. #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Michael Norton
timelineItems.text: Grabavoy out of nowhere sets up Wingert, great punch save to his left on the curler by Konopka #NYCvTOR #TFCLive

timelineItems.name: Armen Bedakian
timelineItems.text: RB Delgado failing to connect with MF Altidore, while ST Bradley attempts to provide an outlet up top for #TFC

timelineItems.title: GOAL: Frank Lampard puts New York City FC in the lead with a spectacular finish

timelineItems.name: MLS Weekly Analysis
timelineItems.text: Both of these teams have good attacking power and subpar defenses. This game should have a ton of action. #tfclive #nycfc #nycvtfc

timelineItems.name: Armen Bedakian
timelineItems.text: Nothing GK Osorio could have done about that one #TFC

timelineItems.desc: New York City FC hosts Toronto FC at Yankee Stadium in this crucial mid week clash.
timelineItems.title: HIGHLIGHTS: New York City FC vs. Toronto FC | September 16, 2015

timelineItems.name: Andy Edwards
timelineItems.text: Hey, Frank Lampard scored. Good to see he still knows how to do that. #NYCFC #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Metro Soccer Nation
timelineItems.text: Andrea Pirlo with the initial chip over the top. Excellent work by @RJallen21 to control it back to Lampard who finishes for #NYCFC

timelineItems.name: Matthew Doyle
timelineItems.text: I'm a #MullinsGotATouch truther. #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Sonya Kondratenko
timelineItems.text: Lampard just scored his first MLS goal! #NYCvTOR http://t.co/WBRGSDiTDk

timelineItems.name: Dylan Butler
timelineItems.text: 24' Pirlo with the ball on a string at midfield, draws huge ovation from the crowd. And a foul from TFC #NYCvTOR #NYCFC

timelineItems.name: Jeff Weisinger
timelineItems.text: Saunders with a HUGE save as we hit the 30 minute mark here in the Bronx. Toronto getting chances now in @NYCFC's 3rd. #NYCvTOR, 1-0, 28'

timelineItems.name: Hudson River Blue
timelineItems.text: The much maligned #NYCFC back line has yet to look out of sorts thru 28 minutes. This is a headline!

timelineItems.name: Sixth Borough Blues
timelineItems.text: 2. Pitch is looking good tonight. Might be different for the boys out there, but, certainly looks good! #NYCFC #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Rick Deckard
timelineItems.text: Big ball of Delgado. Bradley has put 8 yards. He could have made 1-1. #TFC

timelineItems.name: Sixth Borough Blues
timelineItems.text: 30. Hernandez dealing with absolutely everything. He's having a brilliant game. #NYCFC #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Peter Nolan
timelineItems.text: Michael Bradley is great at leading leading the break-not as great at finishing it, with either pass or shot. #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: playforthewin
timelineItems.text: Altidore and Wingert having it out tonight, too. #NYCFC #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Sixth Borough Blues
timelineItems.text: 34. Sloppy passing from TFC gifts NYCFC a throw in half way inside their own half. TFC playing poorly. #NYCFC #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Peter Nolan
timelineItems.text: Pirlo pass for Mullins bounces too high, maestro is dealing tonight. #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Deporte Total USA
timelineItems.text: Así se vio desde las gradas el primer gol de #FrankLampard en la #MLS, el #NYCFC toma ventaja vs #TorontoFC. http://t.co/ELNRJZmkID

timelineItems.name: Grand Hyatt New York
timelineItems.text: Let's go, boys! @nycfc #welcometotheclub #yankeestadium #futbol #bronx #soccer #NYCFC http://t.co/ef0jDQDdP2

timelineItems.name: Michael Leach
timelineItems.text: Altidore looks to be fighting a lack of confidence. He overthinks and takes one too many touches. #TFC #TFCLive #NYCFC

timelineItems.name: playforthewin
timelineItems.text: Love watching Mullins' energy. One of my unexpected favorites of the season. #NYCFC #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Sixth Borough Blues
timelineItems.text: 40. Again Hernandez holds off Giovinco who cant get the ball under control just yards from goal. Great work. #NYCFC #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.desc: Attempt blocked. Michael Bradley (Toronto FC) right footed shot from outside the box is blocked.
timelineItems.title: SHOT: Michael Bradley long range shot deflected for a corner kick

timelineItems.name: Hudson River Blue
timelineItems.text: 42' A Bradley corner comes to nothing for #TFC. The Blues are certainly looking the more comfortable squad.

timelineItems.name: Dan Riccio
timelineItems.text: Start to wonder about how this team is constructed. Its nice to have all these talents, not sure if they fit. #TFC

timelineItems.name: Cristina Todea
timelineItems.text: Jacobson is like a sleeping dragon. In the background most of the time, but wake him up & he turns into fire-breathing powerhouse #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Sixth Borough Blues
timelineItems.text: A really great half from the home side. Everyone doing their job well. Took our chance when it came. Good work. Let's go again! #NYCFC

timelineItems.name: Sixth Borough Blues
timelineItems.text: Imagine if we could play like that every week. We'd be well and truly in a play-off spot. I guess the future is bright. #NYCFC #NYCFCfamily

timelineItems.name: Eric W
timelineItems.text: #TFC have created 9 chances in their last 135 minutes. Feel like Diego Valeri at his best does that regularly by himself. #RCTID

timelineItems.name: Jeff Weisinger
timelineItems.text: The biggest thing to look for this half is to see if the @NYCFC backline can hold for a crucial 45 minutes. #NYCvTOR, 1-0, 48'

timelineItems.name: Sixth Borough Blues
timelineItems.text: 48. Giovinco with another shot that Saunders gets his hands to. TFC making a brighter start to the half. #NYCFC #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Christian Araos
timelineItems.text: Patrick Mullins once again doing a good job of making a nuisance of himself when in defense. #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: ByTheMin MLS
timelineItems.text: 48' - The first chance of the half is for #TFC's Sebastian Giovinco. The Italian international's powerful shot is punched away (1-0 #NYCFC)

timelineItems.name: Christian Araos
timelineItems.text: Great through ball from Pirlo springs Grabavoy but his cross is deflected for a corner. #NYCFC

timelineItems.name: Mike Crampton
timelineItems.text: If anyone still had any doubts, this game proves it: #TFC's designated players don't fit together. Square pegs in round holes all season.

timelineItems.name: Charlie LSR
timelineItems.text: Good game for the Pirlo doubters. #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.desc: Attempt saved. Sebastian Giovinco (Toronto FC) right footed shot from outside the box is saved in the bottom left corner.
timelineItems.title: FREE KICK: Sebastian Giovinco's fires one through the wall

timelineItems.name: Louise Gassman
timelineItems.text: My first time at #YankeeStadium & it's to support #NYCFC! #maytheforcebewithyou http://t.co/NFoQqaMjc6

timelineItems.name: Marshall S. Thompson
timelineItems.text: Hopefully #nycfc can hold on to this 1-0 lead for a desperately needed win. http://t.co/sk8t7OYULH

timelineItems.name: Metro Soccer Nation
timelineItems.text: 60. Giovinco's free kick takes a big deflection and Saunders is forced into the save. Preserves the lead for #NYCFC 1-0 #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Christian Araos
timelineItems.text: 62' Jason Hernandez gets booked for shoving Giovinco in the back. FK in a similar spot from a minute ago for Toronto. #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Blue Meanie Mike
timelineItems.text: Jozy's talent is being wasted on the wing, but he's not good enough to displace Giovinco at ST. #NYCFC #TFC

timelineItems.name: Sixth Borough Blues
timelineItems.text: 63. TFC creating a few chances in quick succession. Scramble in the box, consecutive corners. NYC clear eventually. #NYCFC #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: o_0
timelineItems.text: #NYCFC game to live 1-0 lest go nycfc http://t.co/u9KAU3jXsj

timelineItems.desc: Attempt blocked. Frank Lampard (New York City FC) right footed shot from the center of the box is blocked.
timelineItems.title: SHOT: Frank Lampard attempts to get his second goal of the night

timelineItems.name: Tony Larsen
timelineItems.text: A couple of times Pirlo has outrun Bradley. #NYCFC

timelineItems.name: John Molinaro
timelineItems.text: 2-1 New England in 65th minute. If these scores hold, Revs open up nine point gap on #TFC (who still have a game in hand).

timelineItems.name: Nick ChÃ¡vez
timelineItems.text: Lampard needs to get better contact on the ball with his shots. Is this amateur hour? #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.desc: Attempt saved. Michael Bradley (Toronto FC) right footed shot from outside the box is saved in the top left corner.
timelineItems.title: SAVE: Josh Saunders denies Bradley strike from distance

timelineItems.name: Peter Galindo
timelineItems.text: Andrew Jacobson was the only player who read the shot/pass from Sebastian Giovinco. Not a good sign. #NYCFC

timelineItems.name: Chase Igliori
timelineItems.text: POKU TIME. #NYCFC http://t.co/MVIpcGUBLP

timelineItems.name: Sixth Borough Blues
timelineItems.text: 70. Saunders makes his 7th save of the game. 2 shots from Bradley in quick succession. Great saves. #NYCFC #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Metro Soccer Nation
timelineItems.text: Poku makes an instant impact for #NYCFC. Finds Mullins but called off for offside #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Nick ChÃ¡vez
timelineItems.text: Poku with a big run and gives the ball to Mullins whose shot gets stuffed by Toronto's Goalkeeper. Poku Party just tapped the keg. #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Michael Norton
timelineItems.text: Benoit Cheyrou with an abysmal turnover in his own half there. Absolutely awful outing from Toronto tonight #NYCvTOR #TFCLive

timelineItems.name: Ryan Tolmich
timelineItems.text: Another loud ovation for an #NYCFC sub as Khiry Shelton makes his triumphant return for Grabavoy.

timelineItems.name: Nielli-J Thomas
timelineItems.text: Must win game for #NYCFC tonight lets go @franklampard @Guaje7Villa bang in them goals #YankeeStadium http://t.co/9rWKcGJE1J

timelineItems.name: Christina R
timelineItems.text: Big win on Star Wars night! @NYCFC #NYCFC http://t.co/DKMhKSBKKi

timelineItems.name: Javii Alcaraz
timelineItems.text: @NYCFC May the force be with you ⚽️🙌🏽 #NYCFC http://t.co/dkztFFoP5X

timelineItems.name: Linacre Media
timelineItems.text: Not one of the 33,000 coming to #YankeeStadium tonight? Tune in on @espn at 7:30 p.m. #NYCFC #LinacreMediaEvents http://t.co/jBeE12qXo0

timelineItems.text: Pirlo start vanavond in het rechtsveld. #nycfc http://t.co/E4kI98A61r

timelineItems.text: #nycfc #torontofc #yankeestadium (@ Yankee Stadium - @mlb for Toronto FC vs New York City FC) https://t.co/I84I6M257H http://t.co/vu9rpEe0kN

timelineItems.name: Karen Galdames
timelineItems.text: We want poku :) #nycfc http://t.co/uoPZYGVYKW

timelineItems.title: GOAL: Patrick Mullins puts it in the back of the net to extend lead for NYCFC

timelineItems.name: â
timelineItems.text: So yeah... Wooo #nycfc vs #torontofc . Vermont maple syrup is better than Canadian maple syrup!!!! http://t.co/1LTgSy66wy

timelineItems.name: Kurt Y.
timelineItems.text: Seeing Pirlo being 2nd in on the dogpile makes me so damn happy. #NYCFC

timelineItems.name: Major League Soccer
timelineItems.text: Don't touch that dial, Frank. #NYCvTOR is on ESPN2 right now. http://t.co/5f1vm2CtDk http://t.co/JKZteWaBOI

timelineItems.name: Rob Engelsman
timelineItems.text: SPROTS #NYCFC http://t.co/QRfWUKWBie

timelineItems.name: Jeff Weisinger
timelineItems.text: #NYCFC enter the field here at Yankee Stadium in the Bronx... Kickoff in moments #NYCvTOR http://t.co/zu1UxtRMHj

timelineItems.name: OM HanzG
timelineItems.text: #nycfc #weareone #estamosAqui http://t.co/6eh7LkPbu0

timelineItems.name: John Corbett
timelineItems.text: Wow NYCFC are 13 minutes away from a clean sheet against TFC's vaunted lineup. Josh Saunders had a say. #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Christian Araos
timelineItems.text: NYCFC defense can't stop Giovinco when he runs at them. #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: X
timelineItems.text: Wow. #Tfc is free fall mode. Shockingly bad string of results at the wrong time of the year.

timelineItems.name: Andy Edwards
timelineItems.text: #TFC will be a playoff team, but they're going to play away from home in the knockout round and be gone in 90 min. So did they "make it?"

timelineItems.name: Sixth Borough Blues
timelineItems.text: 83. NYC exploring all different avenues around the box, looking for the right pass. Jacobson tries again, wide again. #NYCFC #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Paul Squire
timelineItems.text: Poku and Shelton are linking up well so far. The #NYCFC offense looks supercharged with them on the field

timelineItems.name: Hudson River Blue
timelineItems.text: 87' Tough challenge by Allen produces a dangerous free kick for #TFC, but Bradley launches over the bar to end the peril. #NYCFC

timelineItems.name: Mark Pshuk
timelineItems.text: Even after tonight's loss, #TFC still has roughly a 95% chance of making the playoffs. And they get last-place Colorado at home on Saturday.

timelineItems.name: Peter Nolan
timelineItems.text: NIc, strong run from Lampard, poor pass from Mix. #NYCvTOR

timelineItems.name: Sonya Kondratenko
timelineItems.text: Getting down to the end of things. #NYCvTOR http://t.co/UQXgRdhB22

timelineItems.name: Hudson River Blue
timelineItems.text: Coulda shoulda been a penalty for #NYCFC-- Angelino hit the deck on the break and gets no love.

timelineItems.name: Nick ChÃ¡vez
timelineItems.text: NYCFC definitely looking better with the injection of youth. Probably wouldn't still be in the game without Saunders though. #NYCvTOR
